cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on image recognition using deep convolutional neural networks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a modified network architecture to improve convergence and reduce training complexity. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses backpropagation techniques to update the parameters of the Gabor functions. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as the paper proposes a novel approach to improve image recognition using deep learning. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely sub-category as the paper deals with image recognition, which is a subset of multimedia.
